The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 February is 39,052 (4,520 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 February, there were 968 new confirmed cases (112.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 February, there were 1,448 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 33% (480 fewer cases).
